1
00:01:18,181 --> 00:01:20,661
This is incredible!
- What's happening in our village?

2
00:01:20,861 --> 00:01:23,701
At this rate, nobody in our
village will be safe anymore

3
00:01:23,821 --> 00:01:26,301
A daylight robbery! Something
needs to be done about it!

4
00:01:26,861 --> 00:01:30,221
He's the victim today. Tomorrow,
it could be anyone

5
00:01:30,421 --> 00:01:34,261
Right! Something needs to be done.
- Where are you guys going?

6
00:01:34,421 --> 00:01:37,341
You come along, too. Or she'll
carry you away too!

7
00:01:43,341 --> 00:01:45,981
Will he help? - He's the only
one in the village...

8
00:01:46,061 --> 00:01:50,621
who can solve the problem. We'll
have to fall at his feet!

9
00:01:50,821 --> 00:01:52,061
Right! You're right!

10
00:01:52,141 --> 00:01:53,941
What happened?
- Are your ears blocked?

11
00:01:54,021 --> 00:01:55,701
No.
- So come on

12
00:01:59,421 --> 00:02:01,861
What's happening? Is it
something scandalous?

13
00:02:01,981 --> 00:02:08,061
Nobody knows. Narayan Dada's son
was carried away by a witch

14
00:02:15,941 --> 00:02:18,061
Look at them! The bloody
herd of sheep!

15
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:19,861
They're here to chew on our
brains, early in the day!

16
00:02:20,101 --> 00:02:22,461
Say we're closed for a fortnight.
- What for?

17
00:02:22,861 --> 00:02:25,141
The DCP's mother's getting
married again

18
00:02:29,181 --> 00:02:33,661
Where are they going?
- They just walked by!

19
00:02:46,341 --> 00:02:49,741
Entry to women is forbidden...

20
00:02:58,021 --> 00:03:03,261
Am I going to walk there to help?
Come here and talk to me

21
00:03:10,061 --> 00:03:12,141
Why are you guys wailing?
What's wrong?

22
00:03:12,461 --> 00:03:15,901
You are our Lord and Master!
Our saviour in trouble!

23
00:03:15,981 --> 00:03:20,341
Why? Where are your other saviours?
- But you are the most powerful!

24
00:03:20,501 --> 00:03:24,301
My son has been carried
away by Kartaniya's men!

25
00:03:25,301 --> 00:03:28,061
Kartaniya? Who's this lizard?

26
00:03:28,341 --> 00:03:32,101
That woman from the cattle market!
- She has abducted his son!

27
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:33,941
Is she going to pickle him?

28
00:03:34,581 --> 00:03:37,661
Are the cops around only to have
photos taken of their shining medals?

29
00:03:38,461 --> 00:03:41,341
Go and tell them that
I've sent you. Dismiss!

30
00:03:41,701 --> 00:03:44,941
We went to the police, sir.
We even mentioned your name

31
00:03:45,021 --> 00:03:47,661
But the witch still wouldn't
spare his son!

32
00:03:49,701 --> 00:03:53,221
So you're at my feet because you're
disillusioned with the police?

33
00:03:53,821 --> 00:03:56,541
I don't poke my nose in
other people's affairs

34
00:03:57,661 --> 00:04:00,861
I fight only my own battles.
Go on now, get going

35
00:04:00,941 --> 00:04:05,821
That witch gets all her help from
the lady in Anpara village, sir

36
00:04:06,661 --> 00:04:10,821
Laxmi's goons are standing in
attendance, to defend them

37
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:16,061
Lawyer...
- Sir?

38
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:18,701
Use the phone. Summon
my kids immediately

39
00:04:19,901 --> 00:04:23,501
No, sir. We ought not to
interfere in this matter

40
00:04:23,741 --> 00:04:25,861
Why not?
- It has to do with womenfolk

41
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:28,541
You never know what twist
the tale might take

42
00:04:30,141 --> 00:04:33,021
Don't you guys knows? Seth
Angarchand's men...

43
00:04:33,221 --> 00:04:38,341
never get involved with women!
And you still come here?

44
00:04:38,461 --> 00:04:40,901
Go away now! Mind your own
business! - Listen...

45
00:04:40,981 --> 00:04:41,821
Yes, sir.

46
00:04:42,221 --> 00:04:46,781
As far as I can see, this is
no ordinary case of women

47
00:04:47,461 --> 00:04:50,301
The lady at Anpara and her children
are involved in this scandal

48
00:04:50,981 --> 00:04:52,781
She's a very stubborn woman.

49
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:56,181
If anyone asks me for help against her,

50
00:04:56,661 --> 00:04:58,301
I'm surely
going to help him!

51
00:05:04,661 --> 00:05:06,621
Sir, call for you

52
00:05:10,141 --> 00:05:13,101
Balli, come home immediately.
- Right, Daddy

53
00:05:13,861 --> 00:05:16,061
lmmediately.
- Right away. Immediately

54
00:05:18,981 --> 00:05:26,181
Hail Lord Hanuman,
Lord of Celibacy...

55
00:05:26,341 --> 00:05:27,501
Phone for you, sir

56
00:05:27,821 --> 00:05:30,621
Shakti, see which fool it is

57
00:05:35,141 --> 00:05:35,981
Who the hell is it?

58
00:05:36,181 --> 00:05:40,221
Your mother was nurturing a spirit
wasn't she? I'm the same ghost!

59
00:05:41,621 --> 00:05:44,061
Brother! It's Daddy.
- Daddy who?

60
00:05:44,141 --> 00:05:44,861
Daddy!

61
00:05:46,781 --> 00:05:51,101
Daddy, talk to brother...
- No. Come here immediately

62
00:05:51,501 --> 00:05:54,181
Right, Daddy. We'll
start immediately

63
00:05:55,821 --> 00:05:57,341
Hold this for a moment

64
00:05:57,741 --> 00:06:00,581
Well? You couldn't recognise
my father's voice?

65
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:02,141
I don't tell my father's
voice either

66
00:06:02,221 --> 00:06:04,301
I'll play your father's
voice for you right now!

67
00:06:04,661 --> 00:06:07,101
Is this the law college
boys' hostel? - Yes

68
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,901
I wish to talk to Jaichand.
- I'll call him

69
00:06:15,261 --> 00:06:16,381
Who is it? Go on?

70
00:06:17,101 --> 00:06:18,621
Didn't you go to college today?

71
00:06:19,541 --> 00:06:20,501
Daddy?

72
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:26,581
I went, came back. And
went again and...

73
00:06:26,901 --> 00:06:30,741
Is that a carrom-board you've
been bouncing off?

74
00:06:31,061 --> 00:06:33,301
I'm going back in the
afternoon, daddy

75
00:06:33,581 --> 00:06:36,621
No, no need to go there.
Come home immediately

76
00:06:36,941 --> 00:06:38,821
No, I'm really going in
the afternoon, daddy

77
00:06:39,141 --> 00:06:41,981
Must you keep raving,
you idiot? Listen to me

78
00:06:42,181 --> 00:06:44,621
We got some important business to
finish. Come here immediately

79
00:07:14,221 --> 00:07:18,541
Wow! All the wealthy men together!
At the poor man's door?

80
00:07:20,501 --> 00:07:25,021
So you're the poor man who abducted
a poor farmer's son?

81
00:07:25,461 --> 00:07:27,901
And you now want to swallow
his piece of land in ransom?

82
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:33,421
Bring that boy here immediately.
- So you've come to take the boy?

83
00:07:33,981 --> 00:07:37,501
He's not coming out, sir.
- He can't? Never mind

84
00:07:38,141 --> 00:07:40,701
We can walk. We'll carry him

85
00:07:41,501 --> 00:07:45,701
No, none of you guys can
take him away from here

86
00:07:46,261 --> 00:07:47,781
We are taking him away

87
00:07:48,341 --> 00:07:51,301
We don't use our expensive footwear
to walk to such places

88
00:07:52,101 --> 00:07:58,381
Sir, this is a cattle-market. I
clean scatter with these hands...

89
00:07:58,581 --> 00:08:01,021
I use this hand to wash my backside

90
00:08:01,301 --> 00:08:03,581
A punch with this one
will stink even more

91
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,701
I'm not standing in the
hot sun for too long

92
00:08:10,861 --> 00:08:12,861
Finish it all up quickly. Let's go

93
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:47,261
Which sonofagun dares take
away the boy from here!

94
00:08:49,421 --> 00:08:53,701
Dammit! Silly bachelors!

95
00:08:55,341 --> 00:08:59,461
How would you know what
heat a woman possesses?

96
00:08:59,741 --> 00:09:04,141
Is there a real man among you
who can sate a woman's thirst?

97
00:09:04,501 --> 00:09:07,101
If there is, step forth, you curs!

98
00:09:07,621 --> 00:09:13,101
I'll show you what it means
to flee with a turned tail!

99
00:09:20,941 --> 00:09:21,861
Get out of the way.

100
00:09:21,981 --> 00:09:23,261
Let go of that child.

101
00:09:32,861 --> 00:09:35,101
These are the people responsible
for all this bloodshed and violence

102
00:09:36,461 --> 00:09:38,781
And the father and the sons ought
to be punished for their crimes

103
00:09:39,661 --> 00:09:40,781
That's all, your honor.

104
00:09:48,341 --> 00:09:51,821
Dear students, today happens to be
Anjali's last day at the college

105
00:09:52,941 --> 00:09:58,101
But it saddens me to say that
an intelligent girl like her...

106
00:09:58,781 --> 00:10:03,661
is abandoning her studies
to settle down in matrimony

107
00:10:04,901 --> 00:10:08,901
However, it is a matter of pride
that Anjali is getting married...

108
00:10:09,341 --> 00:10:13,581
to the Home Minister of our State,
the young Mr Govindrao Pachpute

109
00:10:14,341 --> 00:10:18,461
I therefore extend our heartiest
congratulations to her

110
00:10:19,381 --> 00:10:23,101
We hope there will be fame
and honor in her life

111
00:10:24,181 --> 00:10:28,541
Let us therefore give
her a happy farewell

112
00:10:32,061 --> 00:10:35,741
Anjali, listen...
- What?

113
00:10:35,821 --> 00:10:38,261
Will you please help me?

114
00:10:40,301 --> 00:10:41,501
What happened?
- This

115
00:10:42,621 --> 00:10:44,421
What is this?
- My transfer order

116
00:10:44,821 --> 00:10:47,741
You can have a word with the
Minister and have it stalled

117
00:10:49,061 --> 00:10:50,301
Me?
- Yes, you

118
00:10:50,461 --> 00:10:54,861
Now don't say you can't do it.
- I'll do what I can

119
00:11:10,341 --> 00:11:12,701
Bye. - Bye, take care.

120
00:11:13,261 --> 00:11:15,861
Give it to him on your nuptial
night. Don't forget!

121
00:11:16,221 --> 00:11:18,501
Come. - Bye.

122
00:11:26,821 --> 00:11:29,661
Spray the rose-water,
elephant! Spray it!

123
00:11:30,101 --> 00:11:33,301
Spray the rose-water, elephant!

124
00:11:34,141 --> 00:11:35,261
What sort of a mahout are you?

125
00:11:35,581 --> 00:11:37,501
You can't make the elephant
spray the rose-water?

126
00:11:37,821 --> 00:11:39,261
Give me the cane. I'll show you

127
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:44,181
Sprinkle the rose-water,
elephant! Go on!

128
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:54,261
There, Mother! The rose-water
and also the oblations!

129
00:11:54,381 --> 00:11:57,541
What are you guys watching?
Clean the mess!

130
00:12:02,381 --> 00:12:07,901
Sprinkle the rose-water, elephant!
Sprinkle it! - Sprinkle. - Keep going.

131
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:12,061
Who're you giving those dirty looks?

132
00:12:12,861 --> 00:12:14,861
Who asked you to bring
the elephant here?

133
00:12:15,021 --> 00:12:17,181
I did.
- What are you doing, Ma?

134
00:12:17,581 --> 00:12:19,861
There's work held up in the fields
because the elephant's not around...

135
00:12:20,021 --> 00:12:23,101
and you're holding a farce here?
A circus on display?

136
00:12:23,901 --> 00:12:26,301
Circus? My grand-daughter's
getting married...

137
00:12:26,621 --> 00:12:29,901
if the elephant sprinkles
rose-water, does it become a farce?

138
00:12:30,501 --> 00:12:32,461
Have you forgotten the pride
of the high-caste families?

139
00:12:32,741 --> 00:12:35,181
You call a sacred ritual a circus!

140
00:12:35,701 --> 00:12:38,461
In that case, why don't you get the
elephant to serve the guests...

141
00:12:38,661 --> 00:12:43,901
who arrive at the wedding? The
village will witness the honour!

142
00:12:43,981 --> 00:12:48,381
An elephant serving food!
- Viru! Don't try to play my father!

143
00:12:48,821 --> 00:12:52,741
What the elephant will sprinkle
on the people of Anpara...

144
00:12:52,861 --> 00:12:55,661
I will decide, not any servant

145
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:57,981
But mother...
- Enough! Go inside

146
00:13:00,821 --> 00:13:03,061
Brother Pratap, what's going
on with you around?

147
00:13:03,301 --> 00:13:06,941
There'll be 10,OOO guests! And the
elephant's going to be around!

148
00:13:07,381 --> 00:13:10,661
So you want me to sprinkle
rose-water on the guests?

149
00:13:10,981 --> 00:13:13,941
Oh no, go ahead and build muscles!

150
00:13:14,101 --> 00:13:15,861
I wonder what burden you're
going to carry!

151
00:13:15,941 --> 00:13:19,901
Now look, Vir, if you're irked,
go and tell brother Surajbhan

152
00:13:20,301 --> 00:13:22,741
There's no need to eye my
muscles! Is that clear?

153
00:13:24,221 --> 00:13:25,421
There you go again!

154
00:13:25,781 --> 00:13:27,861
Can't the two of you digest
anything unless you argue?

155
00:13:28,421 --> 00:13:32,021
Vir, you don't want the elephant to
be there at the wedding, right?

156
00:13:32,261 --> 00:13:33,101
Yes, brother

157
00:13:33,301 --> 00:13:36,741
I've stuffed a kilo of cotton
in the elephant's ears!

158
00:13:37,021 --> 00:13:40,061
That's when I brought it here!
Even if a bomb explodes...

159
00:13:40,141 --> 00:13:46,301
the elephant won't hear a thing!
- That's very nice... well done!

160
00:13:46,661 --> 00:13:50,261
Why don't you stuff some cotton
in your mother's ears too?

161
00:13:51,421 --> 00:13:56,701
Remember one thing. It's the
marriage of a motherless child

162
00:13:57,581 --> 00:13:59,421
There'll be not just elephants...

163
00:13:59,781 --> 00:14:01,661
...there will be fireworks
at her wedding too!

164
00:14:02,621 --> 00:14:07,741
We will invite only those people who
will bless her with all their heart

165
00:14:08,581 --> 00:14:11,981
Do you understand that?
My foot you will!

166
00:14:18,301 --> 00:14:20,061
Grandma...
- My princess has arrived!

167
00:14:20,941 --> 00:14:23,901
My darling daughter has arrived!
Come, dear...

168
00:14:25,621 --> 00:14:30,861
I hear the Home Minister's fiancee
had a grand send-off at the college?

169
00:14:31,421 --> 00:14:35,621
Don't poke fun at her! It's
commonplace in colleges nowadays

170
00:14:35,861 --> 00:14:38,021
Studies take a back-seat. Fun
and frolic take centrestage!

171
00:14:38,621 --> 00:14:42,701
Why not? My friends came to see me
all decked up at my wedding too

172
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:44,861
Anjali... how are you?

173
00:14:44,901 --> 00:14:50,541
Oh sure! You married this mountain,
and were laden with gold, isn't it?

174
00:14:51,861 --> 00:14:56,581
Enough. - Where's daddy? - He has
gone to meet the Home Minister

175
00:14:56,821 --> 00:14:59,221
He mustn't have been around, so he
must've stood around like a guard?

176
00:14:59,381 --> 00:15:03,501
The Minister hasn't disappeared!
Get lost! He'll come back

177
00:15:09,581 --> 00:15:11,421
Lord...

178
00:15:13,221 --> 00:15:15,981
Where the hell are they?
- What's up, lawyer?

179
00:15:17,461 --> 00:15:20,821
Send half a dozen men, please.
I can't carry this burden on my own

180
00:15:21,381 --> 00:15:25,341
Really? Listen... lend
the lawyer a hand

181
00:15:26,061 --> 00:15:30,181
Looks like the Home Minister has
sent a lot of gifts... hurry up!

182
00:15:30,581 --> 00:15:32,061
Hurry up and get him out

183
00:15:34,861 --> 00:15:36,141
What happened, brother-in-law?

184
00:15:36,381 --> 00:15:40,141
What happened to him? - Let him get
some fresh air... Get some water!

185
00:15:40,181 --> 00:15:43,821
But how did this happen to him?
- Daddy? What happened?

186
00:15:44,381 --> 00:15:46,861
The cat got your tongue? Won't
you tell us what happened?

187
00:15:48,181 --> 00:15:51,181
All I can say is that this
wedding is not taking place

188
00:15:55,021 --> 00:15:59,301
The Home Minister claims that this
alliance is posing problems for him

189
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:01,461
And I say he's being instigated...

190
00:16:01,621 --> 00:16:03,341
...so that our daughter's
wedding is stalled

191
00:16:03,501 --> 00:16:07,501
Stall my grand-daughter's wedding?
Who dares? Tell me!

192
00:16:07,941 --> 00:16:11,621
It's no good wringing my neck!
Rather you strangle Angarchand's neck!

193
00:16:11,861 --> 00:16:13,221
He's the one who has had
this wedding called off

194
00:16:13,381 --> 00:16:16,661
He has lured ten legislators
to his fold.

195
00:16:16,901 --> 00:16:18,981
He has threatened the
Home Minister...

196
00:16:19,381 --> 00:16:24,061
to call off the wedding, else he'll
be toppled off his position

197
00:16:24,341 --> 00:16:27,221
And that is why he has refused
to go ahead with the wedding

198
00:16:27,581 --> 00:16:32,741
And you know! Death, mosquitoes and
politicians are not to be trusted!

199
00:16:32,981 --> 00:16:38,061
That's it! Bravo! Slam him to
the ground! - Flattened him.

200
00:16:39,821 --> 00:16:43,061
Eat all you want to, let there
be no room in your tummy

201
00:16:43,661 --> 00:16:47,661
There's no feast at Anpara anymore.
- There'll only be a mourning there

202
00:16:48,901 --> 00:16:50,261
They were forging an alliance...

203
00:16:50,341 --> 00:16:52,301
...with the Home Minister
to belittle Angarchand!

204
00:16:52,501 --> 00:16:54,861
And now her own grand-daughter
sits humiliated at home!

205
00:16:56,581 --> 00:16:58,381
I spat because the people of Anpara
have gone down on their knees...

206
00:16:58,581 --> 00:17:00,301
...before me

207
00:17:00,581 --> 00:17:03,821
Why did you have to spit?
One single spit was enough

208
00:17:03,861 --> 00:17:05,581
I spat because you spat
on my face, sir

209
00:17:05,781 --> 00:17:09,421
But you sat before me with
your mouth wide open!

210
00:17:09,701 --> 00:17:12,061
Where else could I spit?
Go and sit elsewhere!

211
00:17:14,101 --> 00:17:19,541
But this is surely not enough.
The story doesn't end here

212
00:17:20,101 --> 00:17:23,061
She'll have to go through
a lot more misery

213
00:17:23,421 --> 00:17:26,541
The mother and her children will
go through a lot more of hell!

214
00:17:27,581 --> 00:17:31,141
Shakti. - Yes. - Are the fireworks
ready? - Yes, daddy

215
00:17:31,301 --> 00:17:33,941
So what are you waiting
for? Burst them

216
00:17:40,181 --> 00:17:43,021
What are you doing, Ma?
Are we all dead?

217
00:17:43,101 --> 00:17:46,221
If you are true men, take
this gun and go there

218
00:17:46,821 --> 00:17:48,421
Bring his dead body to me!

219
00:17:48,501 --> 00:17:52,101
Lady! What madness is this?

220
00:17:52,301 --> 00:17:55,301
Yes! The Ladyship of
Anpara has gone mad!

221
00:17:55,421 --> 00:17:58,901
She has killed Angarchand!
Say that in the court!

222
00:17:58,981 --> 00:18:02,861
Don't just watch! Stop her!
- Ma... stop there!

223
00:18:02,941 --> 00:18:06,941
Watch out! If anyone tries
to stop me, I'll kill him!

224
00:18:07,101 --> 00:18:09,381
Wastrels! Don't get
anywhere close to me!

225
00:18:09,541 --> 00:18:15,181
Stop it, Ma... - Give me the gun. -
Listen to me... Ma.

226
00:18:20,941 --> 00:18:23,821
Get the car out.
- What are you doing Ma? Wait...

227
00:18:23,901 --> 00:18:27,821
have you gone mad?
Calm down! Ma...

228
00:18:28,301 --> 00:18:30,301
Let me go! Leave me alone!
- Calm down, Ma...

229
00:18:30,381 --> 00:18:33,261
have you gone mad? Quiet! Quiet!

230
00:18:36,901 --> 00:18:40,221
Ma... Get some water quickly!

231
00:18:42,261 --> 00:18:47,261
Great! What bigger blow could we
have dealt to them than this one?

232
00:18:47,661 --> 00:18:52,661
Thanks to this, the children of
this place can now live in peace

233
00:18:52,821 --> 00:18:55,981
The children of this
family are already living in peace.

234
00:18:56,461 --> 00:18:57,381
You doubt that?

235
00:18:57,461 --> 00:19:00,861
What sort of a life is this, sir?
Getting violent to help others...

236
00:19:00,981 --> 00:19:04,901
resorting to bloodshed to humiliate
the family in Anpara...

237
00:19:05,141 --> 00:19:07,701
what sort of a life is this?
What I'm getting at is...

238
00:19:07,901 --> 00:19:11,341
they too now need to lead a
decent life too, isn't it?

239
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,421
No!
- I see!

240
00:19:13,901 --> 00:19:16,581
So you're still against
the family in Anpara?

241
00:19:16,981 --> 00:19:18,581
You must end this feud of 20 years...

242
00:19:18,741 --> 00:19:22,861
...and put an end all the
bloodshed and violence

243
00:19:23,101 --> 00:19:25,781
For how long will you keep
the fires of hatred alive?

244
00:19:26,021 --> 00:19:30,741
The fires will live, lawyer! Do
you expect me to forget it all?

245
00:19:31,701 --> 00:19:36,021
Even though the fires are dead,
the embers are still alive

246
00:19:37,061 --> 00:19:40,981
Must I really forget it all? And
how many things must I forget?

247
00:19:41,461 --> 00:19:43,501
Tell me... tell me!

248
00:19:47,021 --> 00:19:50,581
My Parvati... the goddess
of my family

249
00:19:52,101 --> 00:19:56,901
Before my very eyes, she was here
at the altar in this courtyard

250
00:19:58,381 --> 00:20:02,541
And she finally breathed
her last in my arms

251
00:20:03,781 --> 00:20:07,821
Must I forget that? I spent
14 years in prison

252
00:20:08,621 --> 00:20:11,661
I endured the hardships of prison
life mentally and physically

253
00:20:12,581 --> 00:20:13,741
Must I forget it all?

254
00:20:16,101 --> 00:20:19,541
You just said that my children
need to lead a peaceful life

255
00:20:20,261 --> 00:20:24,741
But why isn't that the case? Why
hasn't Balram got married?

256
00:20:25,941 --> 00:20:28,301
Why haven't Kishan and
Shakti got married yet?

257
00:20:29,661 --> 00:20:35,021
After Jai, no child was
born in this family

258
00:20:35,261 --> 00:20:42,301
I always yearned to see a cheerful
baby. Why? Tell me

259
00:20:43,301 --> 00:20:46,861
Angarchand can never forget
all these things. Never

260
00:20:48,221 --> 00:20:51,981
It isn't an iniury on my body.
It's a wound on my heart

261
00:20:53,461 --> 00:20:57,781
My fires will be sated only when
that woman and her children are dead

262
00:21:00,181 --> 00:21:06,221
If pain could be expressed, every
wound of mine would speak volumes

263
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:11,901
Shut up! First think of putting out
the fires that rage in my heart!

264
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:16,221
Only a widow knows the anguish
of losing her husband!

265
00:21:17,021 --> 00:21:21,341
You lost your father, but I did
not concede defeat to Angara!

266
00:21:22,221 --> 00:21:26,381
But today I realize that Angara's
sons are true men. And my sons...

267
00:21:26,901 --> 00:21:30,061
are iackals that hide behind
their wives aprons! Jackals!

268
00:21:30,501 --> 00:21:32,301
Yes, keep saying that
to them, lawyer

269
00:21:32,381 --> 00:21:33,981
Where are you going, Roopa?

270
00:21:34,941 --> 00:21:41,061
Wow! The birds and the bees!
That's the beauty of a woman!

271
00:21:41,941 --> 00:21:44,101
You see how they got drawn away?

272
00:21:44,421 --> 00:21:49,981
Get this clearly! Only a woman can
create a rift in that family!

273
00:21:50,981 --> 00:21:54,181
That there is no woman in their
lives happens to be their strength!

274
00:21:54,421 --> 00:21:58,101
If there were a woman
in Angara's family...

275
00:21:58,661 --> 00:22:00,261
it would difficult
for them to handle.

276
00:22:01,301 --> 00:22:02,941
All four would take
different paths...

277
00:22:04,196 --> 00:22:08,036
and thus, they would be weakened.
You don't get it?

278
00:22:08,556 --> 00:22:13,716
We need a girl to destroy the
discipline of that family!

279
00:22:14,036 --> 00:22:16,156
You will then see...
- Shut up!

280
00:22:16,596 --> 00:22:20,156
Cut the crap! You've
been barking away!

281
00:22:20,516 --> 00:22:23,716
My daughter's weeping because her
marriage has been called off

282
00:22:23,876 --> 00:22:26,876
And this man is thinking about
getting those princes married!

283
00:22:28,156 --> 00:22:31,876
Are you going to kill the girl because
her marriage has been called off?

284
00:22:32,036 --> 00:22:36,276
She says she's not going to study.
- That's what she'll obviously say

285
00:22:36,796 --> 00:22:40,036
But if she remains here, she'll
be even more miserable

286
00:22:40,476 --> 00:22:44,116
So I suggest you ask her to
resume her studies again

287
00:22:44,356 --> 00:22:49,916
The latest! Sensational
news! All for free!

288
00:22:51,076 --> 00:22:53,996
Take it for free.
- How's it going? - Great guns!

289
00:22:55,596 --> 00:22:57,956
Where's the rest of the money?
- What money?

290
00:22:58,556 --> 00:23:01,796
This is not done! You never return
the balance to me ever!

291
00:23:02,076 --> 00:23:03,876
Did I ever ask for
the balance from you?

292
00:23:04,236 --> 00:23:05,916
When did you give me
any money at all?

293
00:23:06,196 --> 00:23:07,796
Don't screw up my mood.
I've got work to do

294
00:23:08,036 --> 00:23:11,076
Sensational news! For free!
Mind-blowing news! Take it.

295
00:23:13,156 --> 00:23:17,356
The village belle returns...

296
00:23:17,436 --> 00:23:22,476
she could not unite
with her beloved

297
00:23:22,836 --> 00:23:26,596
He did not bring the bridal
fineries for her...

298
00:23:26,676 --> 00:23:33,156
so who is she going to find now?

299
00:23:35,916 --> 00:23:39,396
Look at this babe!

300
00:23:39,476 --> 00:23:42,076
Just ask, why's
she so worked up?

301
00:23:42,156 --> 00:23:47,716
Just look, what a babe!

302
00:23:48,716 --> 00:23:51,756
Just look, what a babe!

303
00:23:51,836 --> 00:23:54,756
Just ask, why's
she so worked up?

304
00:23:54,876 --> 00:23:57,836
Just look, what a babe!

305
00:24:01,276 --> 00:24:04,236
Why's she so arrogant? Why does
she fight with everyone?

306
00:24:04,436 --> 00:24:07,196
She seems to be a spirit!

307
00:24:44,356 --> 00:24:47,236
Her charm is a killer

308
00:24:47,516 --> 00:24:50,436
Her eyes ooze oomph

309
00:24:50,796 --> 00:24:56,836
Lightning strikes my heart
when she sways in her gait

310
00:24:56,996 --> 00:24:59,636
She makes everyone
at college pine...

311
00:25:00,076 --> 00:25:02,796
she won't let anyone get
their hands on her

312
00:25:03,116 --> 00:25:08,956
She's a volcano waiting to erupt

313
00:25:09,036 --> 00:25:15,116
Fair-skinned, beautiful...
she's sure a nymph

314
00:25:15,316 --> 00:25:21,476
A blossoming beauty, she's
proud of her looks

315
00:25:21,756 --> 00:25:24,476
Tell her, friends...

316
00:25:24,836 --> 00:25:27,836
not to flaunt her airs

317
00:26:01,676 --> 00:26:04,676
Let's give her happy memories

318
00:26:04,836 --> 00:26:07,716
Let's find a prince for her

319
00:26:08,156 --> 00:26:10,796
The poor girl's grieving...

320
00:26:11,196 --> 00:26:13,956
let's make her a bride

321
00:26:14,356 --> 00:26:17,156
Why's she always on her own?

322
00:26:17,356 --> 00:26:20,036
She's such an enigma

323
00:26:20,556 --> 00:26:26,156
Nobody knows what ails her

324
00:26:26,476 --> 00:26:32,516
Someone reason with her,
she's all pumped up

325
00:26:32,676 --> 00:26:35,556
At this rate, she won't
find anyone...

326
00:26:35,756 --> 00:26:38,596
she ought to get back to her senses

327
00:26:39,036 --> 00:26:44,916
The poor girl might end
up remaining a spinster

328
00:26:58,036 --> 00:27:01,836
I told you folks that I'm not
going back to that college!

329
00:27:02,196 --> 00:27:04,316
But you still thrust
me into that hell!

330
00:27:06,276 --> 00:27:08,196
He humiliated me in front
of the whole college

331
00:27:09,036 --> 00:27:11,636
I've lost all the
respect and honour!

332
00:27:12,436 --> 00:27:14,916
Are you happy now?
- Who humiliated you?

333
00:27:16,676 --> 00:27:19,076
Your Uncle has asked you a
question. Haven't you heard him?

334
00:27:19,516 --> 00:27:23,996
Who else could it be? It was
Angarchand's son, Jai!

335
00:27:25,196 --> 00:27:26,756
He had it published in a newspaper...

336
00:27:26,836 --> 00:27:28,516
...and distributed it
in the whole college

337
00:27:28,636 --> 00:27:30,556
Do you know what filthy things
they wrote about me?

338
00:27:31,356 --> 00:27:33,636
That scoundrel dares?! Brother,
Vir... let's go!

339
00:27:33,996 --> 00:27:36,716
Hari Singh, Deva... get your swords!

340
00:27:36,876 --> 00:27:41,236
Get a dozen more men! After
we're through with him...

341
00:27:41,836 --> 00:27:43,836
he'll never do a thing like this
ever again in his lifetime!

342
00:27:43,956 --> 00:27:47,036
Where do you think you're going?
And what do you imagine?

343
00:27:47,476 --> 00:27:50,756
He'll be waiting for you...
to welcome you?

344
00:27:51,596 --> 00:27:55,756
Remember, you took a battalion last
time to fight over water rights

345
00:27:55,996 --> 00:27:58,116
And what happened? Four
of your men got killed...

346
00:27:58,436 --> 00:28:01,716
Seven were crippled,
four lost an eye...

347
00:28:01,876 --> 00:28:03,556
and five were permanently blinded!

348
00:28:03,836 --> 00:28:05,716
We're still paying for
their livelihood!

349
00:28:05,836 --> 00:28:09,836
Bloody lawyer! You live off us and
lavish praise on that family?

350
00:28:09,996 --> 00:28:12,356
We fought then for someone
else's water rights

351
00:28:12,756 --> 00:28:14,756
But it now has to do with
the honour of our family!

352
00:28:14,916 --> 00:28:17,956
He'll have to pay for toying with
the honour of a girl from our family!

353
00:28:18,396 --> 00:28:21,676
This is too much, Ma. We're now
going to return after beheading them!

354
00:28:21,836 --> 00:28:23,196
Let's go, brother.
- Wait

355
00:28:25,396 --> 00:28:27,476
I don't want you to do anything

356
00:28:27,796 --> 00:28:29,796
Can't you hear me? Go inside!

357
00:28:49,596 --> 00:28:51,076
There's no need to pamper me!

358
00:28:51,796 --> 00:28:53,796
Grandma, I went to college because
I cared for your feelings

359
00:28:53,876 --> 00:28:56,996
But when it came to my honour,
nobody here is bothered about it

360
00:28:57,276 --> 00:29:01,356
All the love just evaporated!
- Who said it evaporated?

361
00:29:01,996 --> 00:29:04,196
Now is when the love
will flow, my dear

362
00:29:04,956 --> 00:29:08,996
Maybe I'm getting old, but I
haven't lost the spirit yet

363
00:29:09,876 --> 00:29:11,756
Then why did you stop my
father and my uncles?

364
00:29:12,196 --> 00:29:14,476
Why didn't you let them
battle it out? But no!

365
00:29:15,036 --> 00:29:18,236
Your sons must come to no harm,
even if I'm burnt in the process!

366
00:29:19,116 --> 00:29:21,036
What do I mean to you anyway?
Why must you bother?

367
00:29:21,516 --> 00:29:23,036
Have you gone mad?

368
00:29:23,916 --> 00:29:26,876
Is that all you have got to know
of your grandma in so many years?

369
00:29:28,196 --> 00:29:31,596
The best attack is the one
that makes the least noise

370
00:29:32,276 --> 00:29:36,276
Listen, did he humiliate me or
your father or your uncles? No

371
00:29:36,556 --> 00:29:40,756
He humiliated you. So you will
plot the course of your revenge

372
00:29:41,036 --> 00:29:46,076
You will fight for honour. How's
he to look at? Handsome?

373
00:29:47,036 --> 00:29:49,196
Who?
- Angara's son?

374
00:29:50,516 --> 00:29:52,396
I don't know, I didn't
look carefully

375
00:29:52,636 --> 00:29:54,956
Then you must now take a good look

376
00:29:55,476 --> 00:29:57,956
You will have to give him
a sense of belonging...

377
00:29:58,156 --> 00:30:01,916
and make him eat out of your
hands. Make him a pet

378
00:30:03,276 --> 00:30:06,036
You mean, I must fall
in love with him?

379
00:30:06,716 --> 00:30:10,596
Love? If you fall in love,
you're the first one I'll cremate!

380
00:30:11,116 --> 00:30:13,396
There's a difference in what you
weigh and what you buy.

381
00:30:13,636 --> 00:30:15,236
You have to just weigh.

382
00:30:15,596 --> 00:30:18,556
You got to lay the trap
of everlasting love

383
00:30:19,596 --> 00:30:21,836
Bring him to a position
where he licks your heels

384
00:30:22,436 --> 00:30:24,476
When he's madly in love with you...

385
00:30:24,836 --> 00:30:27,516
...and revolts against
Angara and his family.

386
00:30:28,196 --> 00:30:30,396
And if you will say,
he'll even present...

387
00:30:30,476 --> 00:30:32,316
...Angara's head to you on a platter

388
00:30:32,636 --> 00:30:35,996
And what love and what alliance?
It'll be the end of the story

389
00:30:36,356 --> 00:30:38,396
He'll bang his head on
the walls all his life

390
00:30:38,916 --> 00:30:43,676
Our revenge will be complete.
Then, I'll have my peace!

391
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:46,396
You get that, little girl?

392
00:30:59,996 --> 00:31:01,876
Listen, where's Jai's room?

393
00:31:02,236 --> 00:31:04,396
Upstairs. Room number 6.
Want me to call him?

394
00:31:05,396 --> 00:31:06,836
No thanks. I'll find him on my own

395
00:31:07,556 --> 00:31:08,316
Hey, move.

396
00:31:09,116 --> 00:31:09,756
Jai!

397
00:31:17,276 --> 00:31:21,436
Jai! Wake up!
- Let me sleep!

398
00:31:21,756 --> 00:31:23,996
That girl's coming here.
- Which girl?

399
00:31:24,956 --> 00:31:26,876
Anjali.
- Don't tell me!

400
00:31:26,956 --> 00:31:28,836
Yes!
- How did she get here?

401
00:31:28,916 --> 00:31:30,636
How would I know? She is here.

402
00:31:30,796 --> 00:31:31,996
Give me my pyiama!
Where the heck is it?

403
00:31:32,076 --> 00:31:33,996
I'm not your wife! - Give me
my pyjama! - Here, take this.

404
00:31:34,156 --> 00:31:36,476
You're on the bed, and your
pyjama's are on the floor!

405
00:31:36,716 --> 00:31:39,836
The girl! Keep her out!
- Hurry up and wear it!

406
00:31:42,956 --> 00:31:45,276
I want to talk to Jai.
- How come?

407
00:31:45,596 --> 00:31:48,436
Jai... I need to talk in privacy

408
00:31:48,636 --> 00:31:51,356
No way! Say what you have
to in his presence!

409
00:31:52,116 --> 00:31:55,276
This is between you and me.
Rather we talk in privacy

410
00:31:57,236 --> 00:31:58,516
Lucky!

411
00:32:01,116 --> 00:32:04,156
Can I come in and talk? - Not
necessary. Speak from where you are

412
00:32:06,516 --> 00:32:09,756
But I'm not comfortable here.
- What're you doing, girl... watch it!

413
00:32:11,556 --> 00:32:14,236
This place is only for men; so come
out and say whatever it is!

414
00:32:19,836 --> 00:32:25,156
I haven't come to stay anyway. But
I will say what I have come to say

415
00:32:26,796 --> 00:32:30,556
What harm have I done to you, that
you're treating me like this?

416
00:32:31,436 --> 00:32:33,756
There is an enemity between
our families...

417
00:32:34,436 --> 00:32:35,996
but must you seek revenge from me?

418
00:32:38,036 --> 00:32:40,156
My marriage was annulled
because of your father

419
00:32:41,676 --> 00:32:44,476
But don't ruin my
studies now. Please

420
00:32:45,596 --> 00:32:49,596
I request you... stop bothering me

421
00:32:51,436 --> 00:32:52,716
Even if we're enemies...

422
00:32:53,476 --> 00:32:57,116
...when a girl cries before
you and asks for your help.

423
00:32:57,876 --> 00:33:02,196
And if you still bother her, it's
terribly shameful for a man

424
00:33:05,116 --> 00:33:08,196
And I really believe that you're
the only man in your family...

425
00:33:09,516 --> 00:33:10,876
who will not disappoint me

426
00:33:16,796 --> 00:33:18,436
Go on... go inside

427
00:33:18,756 --> 00:33:22,236
She shouldn't have said that...
how could she say such a thing?

428
00:33:22,556 --> 00:33:24,796
What?
- She means you're the only man...

429
00:33:24,876 --> 00:33:29,116
in your family, and the rest of
them are impotent, faggots...

430
00:33:29,276 --> 00:33:32,916
so they didn't get married!
- When did she say that?

431
00:33:33,036 --> 00:33:35,996
She said it to your face!
- And I didn't utter a word?

432
00:33:36,076 --> 00:33:38,396
No!
- Did she say that?

433
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:43,036
Did she really? - Yes...
she did. - I'll show her!

434
00:33:48,716 --> 00:33:50,996
Hey girl... what did you say to me?

435
00:33:52,516 --> 00:33:54,316
That I'm the only real
man in the family, eh?

436
00:33:57,356 --> 00:34:00,236
Was I wrong? Aren't you a man?

437
00:34:00,676 --> 00:34:03,556
No!...I mean, I am!

438
00:34:03,876 --> 00:34:08,396
Are the rest of my brothers impotent?
- Really? I just got to know

439
00:34:08,996 --> 00:34:10,556
Is that how things are?

440
00:34:11,636 --> 00:34:14,396
Poor brothers!
- Look, don't act too smart!

441
00:34:14,716 --> 00:34:16,636
Don't mess with Angarchand's
sons, okay?

442
00:34:17,556 --> 00:34:22,556
You'll land in deep trouble!
They're lions... jackals, actually!

443
00:34:22,676 --> 00:34:23,916
One second, one second...

444
00:34:24,516 --> 00:34:27,236
what names are you calling
your brothers, Jai?

445
00:34:28,036 --> 00:34:32,316
You call them lions, iackals...
is it a family or a zoo?

446
00:34:35,956 --> 00:34:38,276
Am I here in the nude? Get lost!

447
00:34:39,396 --> 00:34:41,916
Who do you think you are?
The princess of Anpara?

448
00:34:42,316 --> 00:34:44,916
You're actually a
contagious disease!

449
00:34:45,436 --> 00:34:47,756
This son of Angarchand alone
is enough to deal with you!

450
00:34:48,396 --> 00:34:52,156
I'll give you such a tough time,
I'm going to bother you so much...

451
00:34:53,196 --> 00:34:55,676
I'll do all I can! I
hate you! I hate you!

452
00:34:56,596 --> 00:34:59,876
Have you said what you had to say?
- No! I...

453
00:35:01,836 --> 00:35:04,556
Okay, I have... so?
- Very simple

454
00:35:05,276 --> 00:35:08,476
I'll love you just as
much as you hate me

455
00:35:09,196 --> 00:35:13,516
Keep hissing like a cobra, and
I'll still try to charm you!

456
00:35:15,756 --> 00:35:19,196
Yes, I love Jai. With all my heart

457
00:35:19,356 --> 00:35:22,796
To hell with your heart! I'm not
going to let that happen! Never!

458
00:35:24,036 --> 00:35:26,396
Did you seek my permission
before starting to hate me?

459
00:35:26,756 --> 00:35:28,956
So what's the problem with
my love? It's my choice

